37static const uint8_t kZeroes[EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE] = {0};
38
39// Allow a minute of ticket age skew in either direction. This covers
40// transmission delays in ClientHello and NewSessionTicket, as well as
41// drift between client and server clock rate since the ticket was issued.
42// See RFC 8446, section 8.3.
43static const int32_t kMaxTicketAgeSkewSeconds = 60;
44
45static bool resolve_ecdhe_secret(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs,
46 const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello) {
47 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
48 const uint16_t group_id = hs->new_session->group_id;
49
50 bool found_key_share;
51 Span<const uint8_t> peer_key;
52 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
53 if (!ssl_ext_key_share_parse_clienthello(hs, &found_key_share, &peer_key,
54 &alert, client_hello)) {
55 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
56 return false;
57 }
58
59 if (!found_key_share) {
60 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
61 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_WRONG_CURVE);
62 return false;
63 }
64
65 Array<uint8_t> secret;
66 SSL_HANDSHAKE_HINTS *const hints = hs->hints.get();
67 if (hints && !hs->hints_requested && hints->key_share_group_id == group_id &&
68 !hints->key_share_secret.empty()) {
69 // Copy DH secret from hints.
70 if (!hs->ecdh_public_key.CopyFrom(hints->key_share_public_key) ||
71 !secret.CopyFrom(hints->key_share_secret)) {
72 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
73 return false;
74 }
75 } else {
76 ScopedCBB public_key;
77 UniquePtr<SSLKeyShare> key_share = SSLKeyShare::Create(group_id);
78 if (!key_share || //
79 !CBB_init(public_key.get(), 32) ||
80 !key_share->Accept(public_key.get(), &secret, &alert, peer_key) ||
81 !CBBFinishArray(public_key.get(), &hs->ecdh_public_key)) {
82 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
83 return false;
84 }
85 if (hints && hs->hints_requested) {
86 hints->key_share_group_id = group_id;
87 if (!hints->key_share_public_key.CopyFrom(hs->ecdh_public_key) ||
88 !hints->key_share_secret.CopyFrom(secret)) {
89 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
90 return false;
91 }
92 }
93 }
94
95 return tls13_advance_key_schedule(hs, secret);
96}
97
98static int ssl_ext_supported_versions_add_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs,
99 CBB *out) {
100 CBB contents;
101 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_supported_versions) ||
102 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &contents) ||
103 !CBB_add_u16(&contents, hs->ssl->version) ||
104 !CBB_flush(out)) {
105 return 0;
106 }
107
108 return 1;
109}
110
111static const SSL_CIPHER *choose_tls13_cipher(
112 const SSL *ssl, const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello, uint16_t group_id) {
113 CBS cipher_suites;
114 CBS_init(&cipher_suites, client_hello->cipher_suites,
115 client_hello->cipher_suites_len);
116
117 const uint16_t version = ssl_protocol_version(ssl);
118
119 return ssl_choose_tls13_cipher(cipher_suites, version, group_id);
120}

122static bool add_new_session_tickets(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, bool *out_sent_tickets) {
123 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
124 if (// If the client doesn't accept resumption with PSK_DHE_KE, don't send a
125 // session ticket.
126 !hs->accept_psk_mode ||
127 // We only implement stateless resumption in TLS 1.3, so skip sending
128 // tickets if disabled.
129 (SSL_get_options(ssl) & SSL_OP_NO_TICKET)) {
130 *out_sent_tickets = false;
131 return true;
132 }
133
134 // TLS 1.3 recommends single-use tickets, so issue multiple tickets in case
135 // the client makes several connections before getting a renewal.
136 static const int kNumTickets = 2;
137
138 // Rebase the session timestamp so that it is measured from ticket
139 // issuance.
140 ssl_session_rebase_time(ssl, hs->new_session.get());
141
142 for (int i = 0; i < kNumTickets; i++) {
143 UniquePtr<SSL_SESSION> session(
144 SSL_SESSION_dup(hs->new_session.get(), SSL_SESSION_INCLUDE_NONAUTH));
145 if (!session) {
146 return false;
147 }
148
149 if (!RAND_bytes((uint8_t *)&session->ticket_age_add, 4)) {
150 return false;
151 }
152 session->ticket_age_add_valid = true;
153 bool enable_early_data =
154 ssl->enable_early_data &&
155 (!ssl->quic_method || !ssl->config->quic_early_data_context.empty());
156 if (enable_early_data) {
157 // QUIC does not use the max_early_data_size parameter and always sets it
158 // to a fixed value. See draft-ietf-quic-tls-22, section 4.5.
159 session->ticket_max_early_data =
160 ssl->quic_method != nullptr ? 0xffffffff : kMaxEarlyDataAccepted;
161 }
162
163 static_assert(kNumTickets < 256, "Too many tickets");
164 uint8_t nonce[] = {static_cast<uint8_t>(i)};
165
166 ScopedCBB cbb;
167 CBB body, nonce_cbb, ticket, extensions;
168 if (!ssl->method->init_message(ssl, cbb.get(), &body,
169 SSL3_MT_NEW_SESSION_TICKET) ||
170 !CBB_add_u32(&body, session->timeout) ||
171 !CBB_add_u32(&body, session->ticket_age_add) ||
172 !CBB_add_u8_length_prefixed(&body, &nonce_cbb) ||
173 !CBB_add_bytes(&nonce_cbb, nonce, sizeof(nonce)) ||
174 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&body, &ticket) ||
175 !tls13_derive_session_psk(session.get(), nonce) ||
176 !ssl_encrypt_ticket(hs, &ticket, session.get()) ||
177 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&body, &extensions)) {
178 return false;
179 }
180
181 if (enable_early_data) {
182 CBB early_data;
183 if (!CBB_add_u16(&extensions, TLSEXT_TYPE_early_data) ||
184 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&extensions, &early_data) ||
185 !CBB_add_u32(&early_data, session->ticket_max_early_data) ||
186 !CBB_flush(&extensions)) {
187 return false;
188 }
189 }
190
191 // Add a fake extension. See draft-davidben-tls-grease-01.
192 if (!CBB_add_u16(&extensions,
193 ssl_get_grease_value(hs, ssl_grease_ticket_extension)) ||
194 !CBB_add_u16(&extensions, 0 /* empty */)) {
195 return false;
196 }
197
198 if (!ssl_add_message_cbb(ssl, cbb.get())) {
199 return false;
200 }
201 }
202
203 *out_sent_tickets = true;
204 return true;
205}

207static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_select_parameters(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
208 // At this point, most ClientHello extensions have already been processed by
209 // the common handshake logic. Resolve the remaining non-PSK parameters.
210 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
211 SSLMessage msg;
212 SSL_CLIENT_HELLO client_hello;
213 if (!hs->GetClientHello(&msg, &client_hello)) {
214 return ssl_hs_error;
215 }
216
217 if (ssl->quic_method != nullptr && client_hello.session_id_len > 0) {
218 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNEXPECTED_COMPATIBILITY_MODE);
219 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
220 return ssl_hs_error;
221 }
222 OPENSSL_memcpy(hs->session_id, client_hello.session_id,
223 client_hello.session_id_len);
224 hs->session_id_len = client_hello.session_id_len;
225
226 uint16_t group_id;
227 if (!tls1_get_shared_group(hs, &group_id)) {
228 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NO_SHARED_GROUP);
229 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE);
230 return ssl_hs_error;
231 }
232
233 // Negotiate the cipher suite.
234 hs->new_cipher = choose_tls13_cipher(ssl, &client_hello, group_id);
235 if (hs->new_cipher == NULL) {
236 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NO_SHARED_CIPHER);
237 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE);
238 return ssl_hs_error;
239 }
240
241 // HTTP/2 negotiation depends on the cipher suite, so ALPN negotiation was
242 // deferred. Complete it now.
243 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
244 if (!ssl_negotiate_alpn(hs, &alert, &client_hello)) {
245 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
246 return ssl_hs_error;
247 }
248
249 // The PRF hash is now known. Set up the key schedule and hash the
250 // ClientHello.
251 if (!hs->transcript.InitHash(ssl_protocol_version(ssl), hs->new_cipher)) {
252 return ssl_hs_error;
253 }
254
255 hs->tls13_state = state13_select_session;
256 return ssl_hs_ok;
257}
258
259static enum ssl_ticket_aead_result_t select_session(
260 SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert, UniquePtr<SSL_SESSION> *out_session,
261 int32_t *out_ticket_age_skew, bool *out_offered_ticket,
262 const SSLMessage &msg, const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello) {
263 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
264 *out_session = nullptr;
265
266 CBS pre_shared_key;
267 *out_offered_ticket = ssl_client_hello_get_extension(
268 client_hello, &pre_shared_key, TLSEXT_TYPE_pre_shared_key);
269 if (!*out_offered_ticket) {
270 return ssl_ticket_aead_ignore_ticket;
271 }
272
273 // Per RFC8446, section 4.2.9, servers MUST abort the handshake if the client
274 // sends pre_shared_key without psk_key_exchange_modes.
275 CBS unused;
276 if (!ssl_client_hello_get_extension(client_hello, &unused,
277 TLSEXT_TYPE_psk_key_exchange_modes)) {
278 *out_alert = SSL_AD_MISSING_EXTENSION;
279 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_MISSING_EXTENSION);
280 return ssl_ticket_aead_error;
281 }
282
283 CBS ticket, binders;
284 uint32_t client_ticket_age;
285 if (!ssl_ext_pre_shared_key_parse_clienthello(
286 hs, &ticket, &binders, &client_ticket_age, out_alert, client_hello,
287 &pre_shared_key)) {
288 return ssl_ticket_aead_error;
289 }
290
291 // If the peer did not offer psk_dhe, ignore the resumption.
292 if (!hs->accept_psk_mode) {
293 return ssl_ticket_aead_ignore_ticket;
294 }
295
296 // TLS 1.3 session tickets are renewed separately as part of the
297 // NewSessionTicket.
298 bool unused_renew;
299 UniquePtr<SSL_SESSION> session;
300 enum ssl_ticket_aead_result_t ret =
301 ssl_process_ticket(hs, &session, &unused_renew, ticket, {});
302 switch (ret) {
303 case ssl_ticket_aead_success:
304 break;
305 case ssl_ticket_aead_error:
306 *out_alert = SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR;
307 return ret;
308 default:
309 return ret;
310 }
311
312 if (!ssl_session_is_resumable(hs, session.get()) ||
313 // Historically, some TLS 1.3 tickets were missing ticket_age_add.
314 !session->ticket_age_add_valid) {
315 return ssl_ticket_aead_ignore_ticket;
316 }
317
318 // Recover the client ticket age and convert to seconds.
319 client_ticket_age -= session->ticket_age_add;
320 client_ticket_age /= 1000;
321
322 struct OPENSSL_timeval now;
323 ssl_get_current_time(ssl, &now);
324
325 // Compute the server ticket age in seconds.
326 assert(now.tv_sec >= session->time);
327 uint64_t server_ticket_age = now.tv_sec - session->time;
328
329 // To avoid overflowing |hs->ticket_age_skew|, we will not resume
330 // 68-year-old sessions.
331 if (server_ticket_age > INT32_MAX) {
332 return ssl_ticket_aead_ignore_ticket;
333 }
334
335 *out_ticket_age_skew = static_cast<int32_t>(client_ticket_age) -
336 static_cast<int32_t>(server_ticket_age);
337
338 // Check the PSK binder.
339 if (!tls13_verify_psk_binder(hs, session.get(), msg, &binders)) {
340 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECRYPT_ERROR;
341 return ssl_ticket_aead_error;
342 }
343
344 *out_session = std::move(session);
345 return ssl_ticket_aead_success;
346}
347
348static bool quic_ticket_compatible(const SSL_SESSION *session,
349 const SSL_CONFIG *config) {
350 if (!session->is_quic) {
351 return true;
352 }
353
354 if (session->quic_early_data_context.empty() ||
355 config->quic_early_data_context.size() !=
356 session->quic_early_data_context.size() ||
357 CRYPTO_memcmp(config->quic_early_data_context.data(),
358 session->quic_early_data_context.data(),
359 session->quic_early_data_context.size()) != 0) {
360 return false;
361 }
362 return true;
363}
364
365static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_select_session(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
366 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
367 SSLMessage msg;
368 SSL_CLIENT_HELLO client_hello;
369 if (!hs->GetClientHello(&msg, &client_hello)) {
370 return ssl_hs_error;
371 }
372
373 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
374 UniquePtr<SSL_SESSION> session;
375 bool offered_ticket = false;
376 switch (select_session(hs, &alert, &session, &ssl->s3->ticket_age_skew,
377 &offered_ticket, msg, &client_hello)) {
378 case ssl_ticket_aead_ignore_ticket:
379 assert(!session);
380 if (!ssl_get_new_session(hs)) {
381 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
382 return ssl_hs_error;
383 }
384 break;
385
386 case ssl_ticket_aead_success:
387 // Carry over authentication information from the previous handshake into
388 // a fresh session.
389 hs->new_session =
390 SSL_SESSION_dup(session.get(), SSL_SESSION_DUP_AUTH_ONLY);
391 if (hs->new_session == nullptr) {
392 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
393 return ssl_hs_error;
394 }
395
396 ssl->s3->session_reused = true;
397 hs->can_release_private_key = true;
398
399 // Resumption incorporates fresh key material, so refresh the timeout.
400 ssl_session_renew_timeout(ssl, hs->new_session.get(),
401 ssl->session_ctx->session_psk_dhe_timeout);
402 break;
403
404 case ssl_ticket_aead_error:
405 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
406 return ssl_hs_error;
407
408 case ssl_ticket_aead_retry:
409 hs->tls13_state = state13_select_session;
410 return ssl_hs_pending_ticket;
411 }
412
413 // Negotiate ALPS now, after ALPN is negotiated and |hs->new_session| is
414 // initialized.
415 if (!ssl_negotiate_alps(hs, &alert, &client_hello)) {
416 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
417 return ssl_hs_error;
418 }
419
420 // Record connection properties in the new session.
421 hs->new_session->cipher = hs->new_cipher;
422 if (!tls1_get_shared_group(hs, &hs->new_session->group_id)) {
423 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NO_SHARED_GROUP);
424 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE);
425 return ssl_hs_error;
426 }
427
428 // Determine if we need HelloRetryRequest.
429 bool found_key_share;
430 if (!ssl_ext_key_share_parse_clienthello(hs, &found_key_share,
431 /*out_key_share=*/nullptr, &alert,
432 &client_hello)) {
433 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
434 return ssl_hs_error;
435 }
436
437 // Determine if we're negotiating 0-RTT.
438 if (!ssl->enable_early_data) {
439 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_disabled;
440 } else if (!offered_ticket) {
441 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_no_session_offered;
442 } else if (!session) {
443 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_session_not_resumed;
444 } else if (session->ticket_max_early_data == 0) {
445 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_unsupported_for_session;
446 } else if (!hs->early_data_offered) {
447 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_peer_declined;
448 } else if (ssl->s3->channel_id_valid) {
449 // Channel ID is incompatible with 0-RTT.
450 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_channel_id;
451 } else if (ssl->s3->token_binding_negotiated) {
452 // Token Binding is incompatible with 0-RTT.
453 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_token_binding;
454 } else if (MakeConstSpan(ssl->s3->alpn_selected) != session->early_alpn) {
455 // The negotiated ALPN must match the one in the ticket.
456 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_alpn_mismatch;
457 } else if (hs->new_session->has_application_settings !=
458 session->has_application_settings ||
459 MakeConstSpan(hs->new_session->local_application_settings) !=
460 session->local_application_settings) {
461 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_alps_mismatch;
462 } else if (ssl->s3->ticket_age_skew < -kMaxTicketAgeSkewSeconds ||
463 kMaxTicketAgeSkewSeconds < ssl->s3->ticket_age_skew) {
464 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_ticket_age_skew;
465 } else if (!quic_ticket_compatible(session.get(), hs->config)) {
466 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_quic_parameter_mismatch;
467 } else if (!found_key_share) {
468 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_hello_retry_request;
469 } else {
470 // |ssl_session_is_resumable| forbids cross-cipher resumptions even if the
471 // PRF hashes match.
472 assert(hs->new_cipher == session->cipher);
473
474 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_accepted;
475 ssl->s3->early_data_accepted = true;
476 }
477
478 // Store the ALPN and ALPS values in the session for 0-RTT. Note the peer
479 // applications settings are not generally known until client
480 // EncryptedExtensions.
481 if (!hs->new_session->early_alpn.CopyFrom(ssl->s3->alpn_selected)) {
482 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
483 return ssl_hs_error;
484 }
485
486 // The peer applications settings are usually received later, in
487 // EncryptedExtensions. But, in 0-RTT handshakes, we carry over the
488 // values from |session|. Do this now, before |session| is discarded.
489 if (ssl->s3->early_data_accepted &&
490 hs->new_session->has_application_settings &&
491 !hs->new_session->peer_application_settings.CopyFrom(
492 session->peer_application_settings)) {
493 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
494 return ssl_hs_error;
495 }
496
497 // Copy the QUIC early data context to the session.
498 if (ssl->enable_early_data && ssl->quic_method) {
499 if (!hs->new_session->quic_early_data_context.CopyFrom(
500 hs->config->quic_early_data_context)) {
501 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
502 return ssl_hs_error;
503 }
504 }
505
506 if (ssl->ctx->dos_protection_cb != NULL &&
507 ssl->ctx->dos_protection_cb(&client_hello) == 0) {
508 // Connection rejected for DOS reasons.
509 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_CONNECTION_REJECTED);
510 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
511 return ssl_hs_error;
512 }
513
514 size_t hash_len = EVP_MD_size(
515 ssl_get_handshake_digest(ssl_protocol_version(ssl), hs->new_cipher));
516
517 // Set up the key schedule and incorporate the PSK into the running secret.
518 if (ssl->s3->session_reused) {
519 if (!tls13_init_key_schedule(
520 hs, MakeConstSpan(hs->new_session->secret,
521 hs->new_session->secret_length))) {
522 return ssl_hs_error;
523 }
524 } else if (!tls13_init_key_schedule(hs, MakeConstSpan(kZeroes, hash_len))) {
525 return ssl_hs_error;
526 }
527
528 if (!ssl_hash_message(hs, msg)) {
529 return ssl_hs_error;
530 }
531
532 if (ssl->s3->early_data_accepted) {
533 if (!tls13_derive_early_secret(hs)) {
534 return ssl_hs_error;
535 }
536 } else if (hs->early_data_offered) {
537 ssl->s3->skip_early_data = true;
538 }
539
540 if (!found_key_share) {
541 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
542 if (!hs->transcript.UpdateForHelloRetryRequest()) {
543 return ssl_hs_error;
544 }
545 hs->tls13_state = state13_send_hello_retry_request;
546 return ssl_hs_ok;
547 }
548
549 if (!resolve_ecdhe_secret(hs, &client_hello)) {
550 return ssl_hs_error;
551 }
552
553 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
554 hs->ech_client_hello_buf.Reset();
555 hs->tls13_state = state13_send_server_hello;
556 return ssl_hs_ok;
557}
558
559static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_send_hello_retry_request(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
560 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
561 if (hs->hints_requested) {
562 return ssl_hs_hints_ready;
563 }
564
565 ScopedCBB cbb;
566 CBB body, session_id, extensions;
567 uint16_t group_id;
568 if (!ssl->method->init_message(ssl, cbb.get(), &body, SSL3_MT_SERVER_HELLO) ||
569 !CBB_add_u16(&body, TLS1_2_VERSION) ||
570 !CBB_add_bytes(&body, kHelloRetryRequest, SSL3_RANDOM_SIZE) ||
571 !CBB_add_u8_length_prefixed(&body, &session_id) ||
572 !CBB_add_bytes(&session_id, hs->session_id, hs->session_id_len) ||
573 !CBB_add_u16(&body, SSL_CIPHER_get_protocol_id(hs->new_cipher)) ||
574 !CBB_add_u8(&body, 0 /* no compression */) ||
575 !tls1_get_shared_group(hs, &group_id) ||
576 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&body, &extensions) ||
577 !CBB_add_u16(&extensions, TLSEXT_TYPE_supported_versions) ||
578 !CBB_add_u16(&extensions, 2 /* length */) ||
579 !CBB_add_u16(&extensions, ssl->version) ||
580 !CBB_add_u16(&extensions, TLSEXT_TYPE_key_share) ||
581 !CBB_add_u16(&extensions, 2 /* length */) ||
582 !CBB_add_u16(&extensions, group_id) ||
583 !ssl_add_message_cbb(ssl, cbb.get())) {
584 return ssl_hs_error;
585 }
586
587 if (!ssl->method->add_change_cipher_spec(ssl)) {
588 return ssl_hs_error;
589 }
590
591 ssl->s3->used_hello_retry_request = true;
592 hs->tls13_state = state13_read_second_client_hello;
593 return ssl_hs_flush;
594}
595
596static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_second_client_hello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
597 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
598 SSLMessage msg;
599 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
600 return ssl_hs_read_message;
601 }
602 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_CLIENT_HELLO)) {
603 return ssl_hs_error;
604 }
605 SSL_CLIENT_HELLO client_hello;
606 if (!ssl_client_hello_init(ssl, &client_hello, msg.body)) {
607 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_CLIENTHELLO_PARSE_FAILED);
608 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
609 return ssl_hs_error;
610 }
611
612 if (hs->ech_accept) {
613 // If we previously accepted the ClientHelloInner, check that the second
614 // ClientHello contains an encrypted_client_hello extension.
615 CBS ech_body;
616 if (!ssl_client_hello_get_extension(&client_hello, &ech_body,
617 TLSEXT_TYPE_encrypted_client_hello)) {
618 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_MISSING_EXTENSION);
619 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_MISSING_EXTENSION);
620 return ssl_hs_error;
621 }
622
623 // Parse a ClientECH out of the extension body.
624 uint16_t kdf_id, aead_id;
625 uint8_t config_id;
626 CBS enc, payload;
627 if (!CBS_get_u16(&ech_body, &kdf_id) || //
628 !CBS_get_u16(&ech_body, &aead_id) ||
629 !CBS_get_u8(&ech_body, &config_id) ||
630 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&ech_body, &enc) ||
631 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&ech_body, &payload) ||
632 CBS_len(&ech_body) != 0) {
633 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
634 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
635 return ssl_hs_error;
636 }
637
638 // Check that ClientECH.cipher_suite is unchanged and that
639 // ClientECH.enc is empty.
640 if (kdf_id != EVP_HPKE_KDF_id(EVP_HPKE_CTX_kdf(hs->ech_hpke_ctx.get())) ||
641 aead_id !=
642 EVP_HPKE_AEAD_id(EVP_HPKE_CTX_aead(hs->ech_hpke_ctx.get())) ||
643 config_id != hs->ech_config_id || CBS_len(&enc) > 0) {
644 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
645 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
646 return ssl_hs_error;
647 }
648
649 // Decrypt the payload with the HPKE context from the first ClientHello.
650 Array<uint8_t> encoded_client_hello_inner;
651 bool unused;
652 if (!ssl_client_hello_decrypt(
653 hs->ech_hpke_ctx.get(), &encoded_client_hello_inner, &unused,
654 &client_hello, kdf_id, aead_id, config_id, enc, payload)) {
655 // Decryption failure is fatal in the second ClientHello.
656 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECRYPTION_FAILED);
657 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECRYPT_ERROR);
658 return ssl_hs_error;
659 }
660
661 // Recover the ClientHelloInner from the EncodedClientHelloInner.
662 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
663 bssl::Array<uint8_t> client_hello_inner;
664 if (!ssl_decode_client_hello_inner(ssl, &alert, &client_hello_inner,
665 encoded_client_hello_inner,
666 &client_hello)) {
667 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
668 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
669 return ssl_hs_error;
670 }
671 hs->ech_client_hello_buf = std::move(client_hello_inner);
672
673 // Reparse |client_hello| from the buffer owned by |hs|.
674 if (!hs->GetClientHello(&msg, &client_hello)) {
675 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
676 return ssl_hs_error;
677 }
678 }
679
680 // We perform all our negotiation based on the first ClientHello (for
681 // consistency with what |select_certificate_cb| observed), which is in the
682 // transcript, so we can ignore most of this second one.
683 //
684 // We do, however, check the second PSK binder. This covers the client key
685 // share, in case we ever send half-RTT data (we currently do not). It is also
686 // a tricky computation, so we enforce the peer handled it correctly.
687 if (ssl->s3->session_reused) {
688 CBS pre_shared_key;
689 if (!ssl_client_hello_get_extension(&client_hello, &pre_shared_key,
690 TLSEXT_TYPE_pre_shared_key)) {
691 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_INCONSISTENT_CLIENT_HELLO);
692 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
693 return ssl_hs_error;
694 }
695
696 CBS ticket, binders;
697 uint32_t client_ticket_age;
698 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
699 if (!ssl_ext_pre_shared_key_parse_clienthello(
700 hs, &ticket, &binders, &client_ticket_age, &alert, &client_hello,
701 &pre_shared_key)) {
702 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
703 return ssl_hs_error;
704 }
705
706 // Note it is important that we do not obtain a new |SSL_SESSION| from
707 // |ticket|. We have already selected parameters based on the first
708 // ClientHello (in the transcript) and must not switch partway through.
709 if (!tls13_verify_psk_binder(hs, hs->new_session.get(), msg, &binders)) {
710 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECRYPT_ERROR);
711 return ssl_hs_error;
712 }
713 }
714
715 if (!resolve_ecdhe_secret(hs, &client_hello)) {
716 return ssl_hs_error;
717 }
718
719 if (!ssl_hash_message(hs, msg)) {
720 return ssl_hs_error;
721 }
722
723 // ClientHello should be the end of the flight.
724 if (ssl->method->has_unprocessed_handshake_data(ssl)) {
725 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_UNEXPECTED_MESSAGE);
726 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_EXCESS_HANDSHAKE_DATA);
727 return ssl_hs_error;
728 }
729
730 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
731 hs->ech_client_hello_buf.Reset();
732 hs->tls13_state = state13_send_server_hello;
733 return ssl_hs_ok;
734}
735
736static bool make_server_hello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, Array<uint8_t> *out) {
737 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
738 ScopedCBB cbb;
739 CBB body, extensions, session_id;
740 if (!ssl->method->init_message(ssl, cbb.get(), &body, SSL3_MT_SERVER_HELLO) ||
741 !CBB_add_u16(&body, TLS1_2_VERSION) ||
742 !CBB_add_bytes(&body, ssl->s3->server_random,
743 sizeof(ssl->s3->server_random)) ||
744 !CBB_add_u8_length_prefixed(&body, &session_id) ||
745 !CBB_add_bytes(&session_id, hs->session_id, hs->session_id_len) ||
746 !CBB_add_u16(&body, SSL_CIPHER_get_protocol_id(hs->new_cipher)) ||
747 !CBB_add_u8(&body, 0) ||
748 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&body, &extensions) ||
749 !ssl_ext_pre_shared_key_add_serverhello(hs, &extensions) ||
750 !ssl_ext_key_share_add_serverhello(hs, &extensions) ||
751 !ssl_ext_supported_versions_add_serverhello(hs, &extensions) ||
752 !ssl->method->finish_message(ssl, cbb.get(), out)) {
753 return false;
754 }
755 return true;
756}
757
758static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_send_server_hello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
759 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
760
761 Span<uint8_t> random(ssl->s3->server_random);
762
763 SSL_HANDSHAKE_HINTS *const hints = hs->hints.get();
764 if (hints && !hs->hints_requested &&
765 hints->server_random.size() == random.size()) {
766 OPENSSL_memcpy(random.data(), hints->server_random.data(), random.size());
767 } else {
768 RAND_bytes(random.data(), random.size());
769 if (hints && hs->hints_requested &&
770 !hints->server_random.CopyFrom(random)) {
771 return ssl_hs_error;
772 }
773 }
774
775 assert(!hs->ech_accept || hs->ech_is_inner_present);
776
777 if (hs->ech_is_inner_present) {
778 // Construct the ServerHelloECHConf message, which is the same as
779 // ServerHello, except the last 8 bytes of its random field are zeroed out.
780 Span<uint8_t> random_suffix = random.subspan(24);
781 OPENSSL_memset(random_suffix.data(), 0, random_suffix.size());
782
783 Array<uint8_t> server_hello_ech_conf;
784 if (!make_server_hello(hs, &server_hello_ech_conf) ||
785 !tls13_ech_accept_confirmation(hs, random_suffix,
786 server_hello_ech_conf)) {
787 return ssl_hs_error;
788 }
789 }
790
791 Array<uint8_t> server_hello;
792 if (!make_server_hello(hs, &server_hello) ||
793 !ssl->method->add_message(ssl, std::move(server_hello))) {
794 return ssl_hs_error;
795 }
796
797 hs->ecdh_public_key.Reset(); // No longer needed.
798 if (!ssl->s3->used_hello_retry_request &&
799 !ssl->method->add_change_cipher_spec(ssl)) {
800 return ssl_hs_error;
801 }
802
803 // Derive and enable the handshake traffic secrets.
804 if (!tls13_derive_handshake_secrets(hs) ||
805 !tls13_set_traffic_key(ssl, ssl_encryption_handshake, evp_aead_seal,
806 hs->new_session.get(),
807 hs->server_handshake_secret())) {
808 return ssl_hs_error;
809 }
810
811 // Send EncryptedExtensions.
812 ScopedCBB cbb;
813 CBB body;
814 if (!ssl->method->init_message(ssl, cbb.get(), &body,
815 SSL3_MT_ENCRYPTED_EXTENSIONS) ||
816 !ssl_add_serverhello_tlsext(hs, &body) ||
817 !ssl_add_message_cbb(ssl, cbb.get())) {
818 return ssl_hs_error;
819 }
820
821 if (!ssl->s3->session_reused) {
822 // Determine whether to request a client certificate.
823 hs->cert_request = !!(hs->config->verify_mode & SSL_VERIFY_PEER);
824 // Only request a certificate if Channel ID isn't negotiated.
825 if ((hs->config->verify_mode & SSL_VERIFY_PEER_IF_NO_OBC) &&
826 ssl->s3->channel_id_valid) {
827 hs->cert_request = false;
828 }
829 }
830
831 // Send a CertificateRequest, if necessary.
832 if (hs->cert_request) {
833 CBB cert_request_extensions, sigalg_contents, sigalgs_cbb;
834 if (!ssl->method->init_message(ssl, cbb.get(), &body,
835 SSL3_MT_CERTIFICATE_REQUEST) ||
836 !CBB_add_u8(&body, 0 /* no certificate_request_context. */) ||
837 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&body, &cert_request_extensions) ||
838 !CBB_add_u16(&cert_request_extensions,
839 TLSEXT_TYPE_signature_algorithms) ||
840 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&cert_request_extensions,
841 &sigalg_contents) ||
842 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&sigalg_contents, &sigalgs_cbb) ||
843 !tls12_add_verify_sigalgs(hs, &sigalgs_cbb)) {
844 return ssl_hs_error;
845 }
846
847 if (ssl_has_client_CAs(hs->config)) {
848 CBB ca_contents;
849 if (!CBB_add_u16(&cert_request_extensions,
850 TLSEXT_TYPE_certificate_authorities) ||
851 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&cert_request_extensions,
852 &ca_contents) ||
853 !ssl_add_client_CA_list(hs, &ca_contents) ||
854 !CBB_flush(&cert_request_extensions)) {
855 return ssl_hs_error;
856 }
857 }
858
859 if (!ssl_add_message_cbb(ssl, cbb.get())) {
860 return ssl_hs_error;
861 }
862 }
863
864 // Send the server Certificate message, if necessary.
865 if (!ssl->s3->session_reused) {
866 if (!ssl_has_certificate(hs)) {
867 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NO_CERTIFICATE_SET);
868 return ssl_hs_error;
869 }
870
871 if (!tls13_add_certificate(hs)) {
872 return ssl_hs_error;
873 }
874
875 hs->tls13_state = state13_send_server_certificate_verify;
876 return ssl_hs_ok;
877 }
878
879 hs->tls13_state = state13_send_server_finished;
880 return ssl_hs_ok;
881}
882
883static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_send_server_certificate_verify(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
884 switch (tls13_add_certificate_verify(hs)) {
885 case ssl_private_key_success:
886 hs->tls13_state = state13_send_server_finished;
887 return ssl_hs_ok;
888
889 case ssl_private_key_retry:
890 hs->tls13_state = state13_send_server_certificate_verify;
891 return ssl_hs_private_key_operation;
892
893 case ssl_private_key_failure:
894 return ssl_hs_error;
895 }
896
897 assert(0);
898 return ssl_hs_error;
899}
900
901static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_send_server_finished(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
902 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
903 if (hs->hints_requested) {
904 return ssl_hs_hints_ready;
905 }
906
907 hs->can_release_private_key = true;
908 if (!tls13_add_finished(hs) ||
909 // Update the secret to the master secret and derive traffic keys.
910 !tls13_advance_key_schedule(
911 hs, MakeConstSpan(kZeroes, hs->transcript.DigestLen())) ||
912 !tls13_derive_application_secrets(hs) ||
913 !tls13_set_traffic_key(ssl, ssl_encryption_application, evp_aead_seal,
914 hs->new_session.get(),
915 hs->server_traffic_secret_0())) {
916 return ssl_hs_error;
917 }
918
919 hs->tls13_state = state13_send_half_rtt_ticket;
920 return hs->handback ? ssl_hs_handback : ssl_hs_ok;
921}
922
923static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_send_half_rtt_ticket(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
924 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
925
926 if (ssl->s3->early_data_accepted) {
927 // If accepting 0-RTT, we send tickets half-RTT. This gets the tickets on
928 // the wire sooner and also avoids triggering a write on |SSL_read| when
929 // processing the client Finished. This requires computing the client
930 // Finished early. See RFC 8446, section 4.6.1.
931 static const uint8_t kEndOfEarlyData[4] = {SSL3_MT_END_OF_EARLY_DATA, 0,
932 0, 0};
933 if (ssl->quic_method == nullptr &&
934 !hs->transcript.Update(kEndOfEarlyData)) {
935 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
936 return ssl_hs_error;
937 }
938
939 size_t finished_len;
940 if (!tls13_finished_mac(hs, hs->expected_client_finished().data(),
941 &finished_len, false /* client */)) {
942 return ssl_hs_error;
943 }
944
945 if (finished_len != hs->expected_client_finished().size()) {
946 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
947 return ssl_hs_error;
948 }
949
950 // Feed the predicted Finished into the transcript. This allows us to derive
951 // the resumption secret early and send half-RTT tickets.
952 //
953 // TODO(davidben): This will need to be updated for DTLS 1.3.
954 assert(!SSL_is_dtls(hs->ssl));
955 assert(hs->expected_client_finished().size() <= 0xff);
956 uint8_t header[4] = {
957 SSL3_MT_FINISHED, 0, 0,
958 static_cast<uint8_t>(hs->expected_client_finished().size())};
959 bool unused_sent_tickets;
960 if (!hs->transcript.Update(header) ||
961 !hs->transcript.Update(hs->expected_client_finished()) ||
962 !tls13_derive_resumption_secret(hs) ||
963 !add_new_session_tickets(hs, &unused_sent_tickets)) {
964 return ssl_hs_error;
965 }
966 }
967
968 hs->tls13_state = state13_read_second_client_flight;
969 return ssl_hs_flush;
970}
971
972static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_second_client_flight(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
973 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
974 if (ssl->s3->early_data_accepted) {
975 if (!tls13_set_traffic_key(ssl, ssl_encryption_early_data, evp_aead_open,
976 hs->new_session.get(),
977 hs->early_traffic_secret())) {
978 return ssl_hs_error;
979 }
980 hs->can_early_write = true;
981 hs->can_early_read = true;
982 hs->in_early_data = true;
983 }
984
985 // QUIC doesn't use an EndOfEarlyData message (draft-ietf-quic-tls-22,
986 // section 8.3), so we switch to client_handshake_secret before the early
987 // return.
988 if (ssl->quic_method != nullptr) {
989 if (!tls13_set_traffic_key(ssl, ssl_encryption_handshake, evp_aead_open,
990 hs->new_session.get(),
991 hs->client_handshake_secret())) {
992 return ssl_hs_error;
993 }
994 hs->tls13_state = state13_process_end_of_early_data;
995 return ssl->s3->early_data_accepted ? ssl_hs_early_return : ssl_hs_ok;
996 }
997
998 hs->tls13_state = state13_process_end_of_early_data;
999 return ssl->s3->early_data_accepted ? ssl_hs_read_end_of_early_data
1000 : ssl_hs_ok;
1001}
1002
1003static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_process_end_of_early_data(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1004 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1005 // In protocols that use EndOfEarlyData, we must consume the extra message and
1006 // switch to client_handshake_secret after the early return.
1007 if (ssl->quic_method == nullptr) {
1008 // If early data was not accepted, the EndOfEarlyData will be in the
1009 // discarded early data.
1010 if (hs->ssl->s3->early_data_accepted) {
1011 SSLMessage msg;
1012 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
1013 return ssl_hs_read_message;
1014 }
1015 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_END_OF_EARLY_DATA)) {
1016 return ssl_hs_error;
1017 }
1018 if (CBS_len(&msg.body) != 0) {
1019 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
1020 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
1021 return ssl_hs_error;
1022 }
1023 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
1024 }
1025 if (!tls13_set_traffic_key(ssl, ssl_encryption_handshake, evp_aead_open,
1026 hs->new_session.get(),
1027 hs->client_handshake_secret())) {
1028 return ssl_hs_error;
1029 }
1030 }
1031 hs->tls13_state = state13_read_client_encrypted_extensions;
1032 return ssl_hs_ok;
1033}
1034
1035static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_client_encrypted_extensions(
1036 SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1037 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1038 // For now, only one extension uses client EncryptedExtensions. This function
1039 // may be generalized if others use it in the future.
1040 if (hs->new_session->has_application_settings &&
1041 !ssl->s3->early_data_accepted) {
1042 SSLMessage msg;
1043 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
1044 return ssl_hs_read_message;
1045 }
1046 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_ENCRYPTED_EXTENSIONS)) {
1047 return ssl_hs_error;
1048 }
1049
1050 CBS body = msg.body, extensions;
1051 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&body, &extensions) ||
1052 CBS_len(&body) != 0) {
1053 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
1054 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
1055 return ssl_hs_error;
1056 }
1057
1058 // Parse out the extensions.
1059 bool have_application_settings = false;
1060 CBS application_settings;
1061 SSL_EXTENSION_TYPE ext_types[] = {{TLSEXT_TYPE_application_settings,
1062 &have_application_settings,
1063 &application_settings}};
1064 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
1065 if (!ssl_parse_extensions(&extensions, &alert, ext_types,
1066 /*ignore_unknown=*/false)) {
1067 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
1068 return ssl_hs_error;
1069 }
1070
1071 if (!have_application_settings) {
1072 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_MISSING_EXTENSION);
1073 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_MISSING_EXTENSION);
1074 return ssl_hs_error;
1075 }
1076
1077 // Note that, if 0-RTT was accepted, these values will already have been
1078 // initialized earlier.
1079 if (!hs->new_session->peer_application_settings.CopyFrom(
1080 application_settings) ||
1081 !ssl_hash_message(hs, msg)) {
1082 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
1083 return ssl_hs_error;
1084 }
1085
1086 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
1087 }
1088
1089 hs->tls13_state = state13_read_client_certificate;
1090 return ssl_hs_ok;
1091}
1092
1093static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_client_certificate(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1094 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1095 if (!hs->cert_request) {
1096 if (!ssl->s3->session_reused) {
1097 // OpenSSL returns X509_V_OK when no certificates are requested. This is
1098 // classed by them as a bug, but it's assumed by at least NGINX. (Only do
1099 // this in full handshakes as resumptions should carry over the previous
1100 // |verify_result|, though this is a no-op because servers do not
1101 // implement the client's odd soft-fail mode.)
1102 hs->new_session->verify_result = X509_V_OK;
1103 }
1104
1105 // Skip this state.
1106 hs->tls13_state = state13_read_channel_id;
1107 return ssl_hs_ok;
1108 }
1109
1110 const bool allow_anonymous =
1111 (hs->config->verify_mode & SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT) == 0;
1112 SSLMessage msg;
1113 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
1114 return ssl_hs_read_message;
1115 }
1116 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_CERTIFICATE) ||
1117 !tls13_process_certificate(hs, msg, allow_anonymous) ||
1118 !ssl_hash_message(hs, msg)) {
1119 return ssl_hs_error;
1120 }
1121
1122 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
1123 hs->tls13_state = state13_read_client_certificate_verify;
1124 return ssl_hs_ok;
1125}
1126
1127static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_client_certificate_verify(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1128 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1129 if (sk_CRYPTO_BUFFER_num(hs->new_session->certs.get()) == 0) {
1130 // Skip this state.
1131 hs->tls13_state = state13_read_channel_id;
1132 return ssl_hs_ok;
1133 }
1134
1135 SSLMessage msg;
1136 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
1137 return ssl_hs_read_message;
1138 }
1139
1140 switch (ssl_verify_peer_cert(hs)) {
1141 case ssl_verify_ok:
1142 break;
1143 case ssl_verify_invalid:
1144 return ssl_hs_error;
1145 case ssl_verify_retry:
1146 hs->tls13_state = state13_read_client_certificate_verify;
1147 return ssl_hs_certificate_verify;
1148 }
1149
1150 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_CERTIFICATE_VERIFY) ||
1151 !tls13_process_certificate_verify(hs, msg) ||
1152 !ssl_hash_message(hs, msg)) {
1153 return ssl_hs_error;
1154 }
1155
1156 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
1157 hs->tls13_state = state13_read_channel_id;
1158 return ssl_hs_ok;
1159}
1160
1161static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_channel_id(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1162 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1163 if (!ssl->s3->channel_id_valid) {
1164 hs->tls13_state = state13_read_client_finished;
1165 return ssl_hs_ok;
1166 }
1167
1168 SSLMessage msg;
1169 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
1170 return ssl_hs_read_message;
1171 }
1172 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_CHANNEL_ID) ||
1173 !tls1_verify_channel_id(hs, msg) ||
1174 !ssl_hash_message(hs, msg)) {
1175 return ssl_hs_error;
1176 }
1177
1178 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
1179 hs->tls13_state = state13_read_client_finished;
1180 return ssl_hs_ok;
1181}
1182
1183static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_client_finished(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1184 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1185 SSLMessage msg;
1186 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
1187 return ssl_hs_read_message;
1188 }
1189 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_FINISHED) ||
1190 // If early data was accepted, we've already computed the client Finished
1191 // and derived the resumption secret.
1192 !tls13_process_finished(hs, msg, ssl->s3->early_data_accepted) ||
1193 // evp_aead_seal keys have already been switched.
1194 !tls13_set_traffic_key(ssl, ssl_encryption_application, evp_aead_open,
1195 hs->new_session.get(),
1196 hs->client_traffic_secret_0())) {
1197 return ssl_hs_error;
1198 }
1199
1200 if (!ssl->s3->early_data_accepted) {
1201 if (!ssl_hash_message(hs, msg) ||
1202 !tls13_derive_resumption_secret(hs)) {
1203 return ssl_hs_error;
1204 }
1205
1206 // We send post-handshake tickets as part of the handshake in 1-RTT.
1207 hs->tls13_state = state13_send_new_session_ticket;
1208 } else {
1209 // We already sent half-RTT tickets.
1210 hs->tls13_state = state13_done;
1211 }
1212
1213 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
1214 return ssl_hs_ok;
1215}
1216
1217static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_send_new_session_ticket(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1218 bool sent_tickets;
1219 if (!add_new_session_tickets(hs, &sent_tickets)) {
1220 return ssl_hs_error;
1221 }
1222
1223 hs->tls13_state = state13_done;
1224 // In TLS 1.3, the NewSessionTicket isn't flushed until the server performs a
1225 // write, to prevent a non-reading client from causing the server to hang in
1226 // the case of a small server write buffer. Consumers which don't write data
1227 // to the client will need to do a zero-byte write if they wish to flush the
1228 // tickets.
1229 if (hs->ssl->quic_method != nullptr && sent_tickets) {
1230 return ssl_hs_flush;
1231 }
1232 return ssl_hs_ok;
1233}
1234
1235enum ssl_hs_wait_t tls13_server_handshake(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1236 while (hs->tls13_state != state13_done) {
1237 enum ssl_hs_wait_t ret = ssl_hs_error;
1238 enum tls13_server_hs_state_t state =
1239 static_cast<enum tls13_server_hs_state_t>(hs->tls13_state);
1240 switch (state) {
1241 case state13_select_parameters:
1242 ret = do_select_parameters(hs);
1243 break;
1244 case state13_select_session:
1245 ret = do_select_session(hs);
1246 break;
1247 case state13_send_hello_retry_request:
1248 ret = do_send_hello_retry_request(hs);
1249 break;
1250 case state13_read_second_client_hello:
1251 ret = do_read_second_client_hello(hs);
1252 break;
1253 case state13_send_server_hello:
1254 ret = do_send_server_hello(hs);
1255 break;
1256 case state13_send_server_certificate_verify:
1257 ret = do_send_server_certificate_verify(hs);
1258 break;
1259 case state13_send_server_finished:
1260 ret = do_send_server_finished(hs);
1261 break;
1262 case state13_send_half_rtt_ticket:
1263 ret = do_send_half_rtt_ticket(hs);
1264 break;
1265 case state13_read_second_client_flight:
1266 ret = do_read_second_client_flight(hs);
1267 break;
1268 case state13_process_end_of_early_data:
1269 ret = do_process_end_of_early_data(hs);
1270 break;
1271 case state13_read_client_encrypted_extensions:
1272 ret = do_read_client_encrypted_extensions(hs);
1273 break;
1274 case state13_read_client_certificate:
1275 ret = do_read_client_certificate(hs);
1276 break;
1277 case state13_read_client_certificate_verify:
1278 ret = do_read_client_certificate_verify(hs);
1279 break;
1280 case state13_read_channel_id:
1281 ret = do_read_channel_id(hs);
1282 break;
1283 case state13_read_client_finished:
1284 ret = do_read_client_finished(hs);
1285 break;
1286 case state13_send_new_session_ticket:
1287 ret = do_send_new_session_ticket(hs);
1288 break;
1289 case state13_done:
1290 ret = ssl_hs_ok;
1291 break;
1292 }
1293
1294 if (hs->tls13_state != state) {
1295 ssl_do_info_callback(hs->ssl, SSL_CB_ACCEPT_LOOP, 1);
1296 }
1297
1298 if (ret != ssl_hs_ok) {
1299 return ret;
1300 }
1301 }
1302
1303 return ssl_hs_ok;
1304}

1306const char *tls13_server_handshake_state(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1307 enum tls13_server_hs_state_t state =
1308 static_cast<enum tls13_server_hs_state_t>(hs->tls13_state);
1309 switch (state) {
1310 case state13_select_parameters:
1311 return "TLS 1.3 server select_parameters";
1312 case state13_select_session:
1313 return "TLS 1.3 server select_session";
1314 case state13_send_hello_retry_request:
1315 return "TLS 1.3 server send_hello_retry_request";
1316 case state13_read_second_client_hello:
1317 return "TLS 1.3 server read_second_client_hello";
1318 case state13_send_server_hello:
1319 return "TLS 1.3 server send_server_hello";
1320 case state13_send_server_certificate_verify:
1321 return "TLS 1.3 server send_server_certificate_verify";
1322 case state13_send_half_rtt_ticket:
1323 return "TLS 1.3 server send_half_rtt_ticket";
1324 case state13_send_server_finished:
1325 return "TLS 1.3 server send_server_finished";
1326 case state13_read_second_client_flight:
1327 return "TLS 1.3 server read_second_client_flight";
1328 case state13_process_end_of_early_data:
1329 return "TLS 1.3 server process_end_of_early_data";
1330 case state13_read_client_encrypted_extensions:
1331 return "TLS 1.3 server read_client_encrypted_extensions";
1332 case state13_read_client_certificate:
1333 return "TLS 1.3 server read_client_certificate";
1334 case state13_read_client_certificate_verify:
1335 return "TLS 1.3 server read_client_certificate_verify";
1336 case state13_read_channel_id:
1337 return "TLS 1.3 server read_channel_id";
1338 case state13_read_client_finished:
1339 return "TLS 1.3 server read_client_finished";
1340 case state13_send_new_session_ticket:
1341 return "TLS 1.3 server send_new_session_ticket";
1342 case state13_done:
1343 return "TLS 1.3 server done";
1344 }
1345
1346 return "TLS 1.3 server unknown";
1347}
